Three submarines of the [[United States Navy]] have been named '''USS ''Tang''''', after the [[Acanthuridae|tang]], or surgeonfish, especially of the several West Indian species.  May refer to:
* {{USS|Tang|SS-306}}, a {{sclass-|Balao|submarine|2}} sunk by her own torpedo during [[World War II]]
* {{USS|Tang|SS-563}}, the lead boat of [[Tang-class_submarine|her class]], served through the first half of the [[Cold War]]
* {{USS|Tang|SSN-805}}, a planned {{sclass-|Virginia|submarine|2}}

