In 1989, the [[National Film Registry]] selected it for preservation in the United States [[Library of Congress]] as &quot;culturally, historically, or aesthetically significant&quot;.&lt;ref name=&quot;:0&quot; /&gt;

[[American Film Institute]] included the film as #37 in its 1998 [[AFI's 100 Years... 100 Movies]], as #11 in its 2006 [[AFI's 100 Years... 100 Cheers]], and as #37 in its 2007 [[AFI's 100 Years... 100 Movies (10th Anniversary Edition)]].

==Radio adaptation==
On April 17, 1949, ''[[Screen Directors Playhouse]]'' presented ''The Best Years of Our Lives'' on [[NBC]]. Andrews and [[Janet Waldo]] starred in the half-hour adaptation.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal |title=Those Were the Days |journal=Nostalgia Digest |date=Autumn 2012 |volume=38 |issue=4 |page=35}}&lt;/ref&gt;

